h2.span: Overall issues and pull requests status

div.div: Refactor configuration management: Introduce centralized configuration system with constants and validation. Update translation and job processing logic to utilize new config structure. Enhance error handling and logging throughout the application.

Add chapter formatting reprocess endpoint and logic
Introduces a new POST /api/translation/reprocess/:jobId endpoint to re-apply formatting to completed chapters using updated translation options. Implements backend queueing and worker logic for reprocessing, enhances post-processing rules for dialogue splitting, and updates the frontend to allow users to trigger reprocessing for all or selected chapters. Also updates UI to reflect the new 'reprocessing' status.

Improve dialogue formatting and UI label classes
Added new post-processing rules in translationWorker.js to insert line breaks between consecutive dialogue quotes and after dialogue-ending punctuation. Commented out the app stats query in DashboardPage.js. Fixed label class names in TranslationPage.js by removing redundant 'flex' class for consistency.

Refactor translation post-processing and update worker stats interval
Moved and enhanced the translation post-processing logic from deepseekService.js to translationWorker.js, providing more robust and modular formatting and cleanup for translated text. The worker stats polling interval in the frontend was increased from 5 seconds to 60 seconds to reduce API call frequency. This refactor improves maintainability and debugging of translation formatting.
